<div class="collapsible-block-content"><br />
<a href="http://visual-records.wdfiles.com/local--files/scps/scp-075.jpg"><img src="http://visual-records.wdfiles.com/local--files/scps/scp-075.jpg" alt="scp-075.jpg" class="image" /></a>
<p>Cue <a href="http://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/DavidAttenborough">David Attenborough</a>:<br />
And here we have a prime specimen of the great <a href="/scp-075">corrosive snail</a> finishing off its latest kill in the lush wetlands of its native homeworld. This balmy area sees as much as 11&#160;cm of rain per year, and the corrosive snail has evolved to make the most of the prey this bounty attracts. Its powerful digestive acid dissolves all edible material into base chemicals for easy consumption, even the bones; what is not metabolized immediately is compressed and stored within the shell. When the floodwaters recede and the humidity once again drops below 1%, the snail will return to dormancy, living off these copious reserves while patiently waiting for clouds to once again eclipse the blistering twin suns and summon a new feast.</p>
</div>
</div>
