<div class="amberscreen">
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">SCP-1692&nbsp;(Came&nbsp;Back&nbsp;Haunted)</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">♫You&nbsp;grab&nbsp;a&nbsp;line&nbsp;and&nbsp;I'll&nbsp;grab&nbsp;a&nbsp;pole♫</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>♫and we'll head down to the dead stuff hole&#8230;♫</p>
<div class="image-container aligncenter"><a href="http://visual-records.wdfiles.com/local--files/scps/SCP-1692.jpg"><img src="http://visual-records.wdfiles.com/local--files/scps/SCP-1692.jpg" alt="SCP-1692.jpg" class="image" /></a></div>
<p>Foxes have red eyes, breath carbon dioxide, and talk, right? Eh, close enough.<br />
Keep practicing, freaky sinkhole in a swamp with unknown motives. You'll get it right eventually.</p>
<p>I freely admit this one stumped me for a while. On top of the hard-to-pin-down effect, I didn't want to just crib off the awesome page image. I also wanted to do something with its current status, where now it's settling for trying to replicate animals. Think this does the job of capturing the idea, but I might have to revisit this scip at some point.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
