<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Oh&nbsp;yeah.&nbsp;We&nbsp;got&nbsp;plenty&nbsp;of&nbsp;shoggoth.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div class="image-container aligncenter"><a href="http://visual-records.wdfiles.com/local--files/scps/SCP-2102.jpg"><img src="http://visual-records.wdfiles.com/local--files/scps/SCP-2102.jpg" alt="SCP-2102.jpg" class="image" /></a></div>
<p>With this one I tried a technique I'd been wanting to test drive for a while; started out mocking up the hallway, lighting, and the shoggoth with basic 3d shapes and some textures in Blender, and did a quick and dirty render to use as the base for the painting. Not much of that ended up in the final image, but it did help plan out the screwy fisheye perspective I needed for this one, and being able to play with the lighting in advance saved some time on the palette mixing side. Not a game changer, but a nice tool to have.</p>
<p>Still want to know if I screwed up the Russian on that sign or not. That's the sort of thing that bothers me and I only sort-of read that particular language. X3</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="amberscreen">
